What is the meaning behind Orkney’s mysterious stone circles? How far back does the history of the Orkney archipelago truly stretch? What makes its ancient neolithic remains so extraordinary? When were the Picts in Orkney and how did they relate to the politics of Scottish history? What happened when the Vikings arrived in Orkney? When was Orkney Christianised? Who was the legendary patron saint of Orkney, King Magnus, and why was he murdered? Why did Denmark mortgage Orkney to the Scottish crown during the medieval period? Why was Napoleon Bonaparte so interested in Orkney? And, what made Orkney crucial during the Second World War?
In this week’s bonus episode, Tom is joined by historian Peter Marshall to discuss his book (and Tom’s book of the year), Storm’s Edge, and the fascinating history and myths of Orkney, through to the early modern period.
